        <dc:title>ActiveMQ in Action</dc:title>
        <dc:creator opf:file-as="Bruce Snyder, Dejan Bosanac, Rob Davies" opf:role="aut">Bruce Snyder, Dejan Bosanac, Rob Davies</dc:creator>
        <dc:contributor opf:file-as="calibre" opf:role="bkp">calibre (8.3.0) [https://calibre-ebook.com]</dc:contributor>
        <dc:date>2011-03-08T08:07:28+00:00</dc:date>
        <dc:description>&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p style="font-weight: 300; font-family: 'Lato','-apple-system','BlinkMacSystemFont','avenir next','avenir','helvetica neue','helvetica','Ubuntu','roboto','noto','segoe ui','arial','sans-serif'; font-size: 17px"&gt;&lt;em style="color: #333333"&gt;ActiveMQ in Action&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333"&gt; is all you'll need to master ActiveMQ. It starts from the anatomy of a JMS message and moves quickly through connectors, message persistence, authentication, and authorization. By following a running example (a stock portfolio app), you'll pick up the best practices distilled by the authors from their long and deep involvement with this technology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dc:description>
